  "_comment": "Two tiers. body-fetchable = free/wire; fetch full text, write from. headline-only = paywalled; use headlines/deks as newsworthiness signal only, NEVER fetch bodies, NEVER quote. 'authority' weights the cluster score. 'lean' is an AllSides-informed bias label (left | lean-left | center | lean-right | right) used downstream to anchor framing in wires and to balance partisan sources. 'mandate: true' marks outlets whose coverage is treated as editorial vote for 'is this a WSJ-style top story' — coverage in mandate outlets drives the signal_boost factor in scoring (see PIPELINE.md Step 5). Only set mandate on desks that are tightly money/power focused; avoid general-interest desks that run human-interest. AP and Reuters are accessed via Google News site-filter RSS because their native RSS is unreliable; the item link redirects to the real apnews.com / reuters.com article, which WebFetch can follow.",
